  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In gustatory research, for example, imbalanced datasets can result in overfitting to dominant taste categories, such as sweet or salty, while underrepresenting subtle or culturally specific flavors.",
    "In olfactory studies, small datasets may prevent the model from learning the nuanced relationships between molecular structure and perceived odor, leading to poor generalization.",
    "Furthermore, many datasets lack the necessary metadata to contextualize sensory data, such as the cultural background or physiological state of the subjects, making it difficult to interpret model performance across populations.",
    "Generalizability presents another critical limitation (Ektefaie et al. 2024).",
    "Even when AI systems perform well on benchmark datasets, they may fail when applied in different sensory environments or population groups."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Generalizability presents another critical limitation (Ektefaie et al. 2024)."
  ]
}